Sentencas: Ni impregnated 430L anodes used for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells are prepared and evaluated.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni and Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ (SDC) impregnated 430L anodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of catalysts loadings and heat treatment temperatures on the anode polarization resistances are investigated.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni and Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ (SDC) impregnated 430L anodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The stabilities of the Ni impregnated 430L anodes are also measured and increasing the calcination temperature can enable a much more stable anode performance.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni and Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ (SDC) impregnated 430L anodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, by applying the Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) impregnated 430L composite anode, a low polarization resistance of 0.12 Omega cm(2) at 650 degrees C is obtained.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni and Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ (SDC) impregnated 430L anodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 1200 h durability test shows that the polarization resistance of the composite anode increases from 0.12 Omega cm(2) to 0.3 Omega cm(2) during the initial 500 h while no degradation is found during the subsequent measurement.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni and Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ (SDC) impregnated 430L anodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells
